## Getting Started

Make sure you have `node` and `typst` installed (the `sci` CLI installs them via `sci doctor` if you haven't already).

```bash
cd {{.ProjectName}}/
sci proj render        # build pdfs/main.pdf
sci proj preview       # live-preview HTML server
```

Or, equivalently, call MyST directly:

```bash
npx mystmd build --pdf   # one-shot PDF build
npx mystmd start         # live-preview server
```

## Project Structure

```
main.md                # the manuscript body (Intro / Methods / Results / Discussion)
myst.yml               # MyST project config — authors, parts, exports
references.bib         # BibTeX references — cite with {cite}`key`
sections/
    abstract.md        # short summary printed under the title block
    keypoints.md       # bulleted highlights above the abstract
    acknowledgements.md
    opendata.md        # data/code availability statement
figures/               # put figures here, reference with ![](figures/foo.png)
sci-preprint/          # the local Typst template — fully editable
    template.typ       # the actual layout — restyle freely
    template.yml       # template metadata (jtex spec)
    orcid.svg, LICENSE
pdfs/                  # output PDFs (gitignored)
```

## Editing the layout

This project ships a local copy of the `sci-preprint` Typst template at `sci-preprint/`. Edit `sci-preprint/template.typ` to change fonts, margins, the title block, etc. — your changes apply only to this manuscript.

## Submission knobs

`myst.yml` lists the toggles for line numbers, anonymization, and title pages. Add a second export entry to produce an anonymous PDF in parallel:

```yaml
- format: typst
  template: ./sci-preprint
  output: pdfs/main-anonymous.pdf
  anonymize: true
  title_page: true
```
